\title{Transitive relation}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-09}
\taxon{definition}
\meta{source}{[[paul-r-halmos]] [[halmos-1974-naive]] Ch.7}
\MML{relat_2}{def 16}{V8}

\p{Let #{R} be a relation, let #{F} be its [field](nst-000X). We say #{R} is \define{Transitive} if for all #{x\in F}, #{y\in F}, and #{z\in F}, if #{(x,y)\in R} and #{(y,z)\in R}, then #{(x,z)\in R}.}
